<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><TimeML><TIMEX3 tid="t0" functionInDocument="CREATION_TIME"/>Handguns were <EVENT eid="e1" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">used</EVENT> in almost one million crimes  in the United States in <TIMEX3 tid="t1" type="DATE">1992</TIMEX3>, a record, although violent crime in general was  on the decrease, <EVENT eid="e2" class="REPORTING" tense="PRESPART" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">according</EVENT> to a Justice Department report <EVENT eid="e3" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PASTPART" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">released</EVENT> <TIMEX3 tid="t2" type="DATE">Sunday</TIMEX3>.&#13;
Handguns were <EVENT eid="e4" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">used</EVENT> in 917,500 non-fatal crimes in <TIMEX3 tid="t3" type="DATE">1992</TIMEX3>, a 50 percent  <EVENT eid="e5" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">increase</EVENT> over the average for <TIMEX3 tid="t4" type="DURATION">the previous five years</TIMEX3>.&#13;
